Rose Dione https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rose_Dione 0 Claudine Rosalie Gras, October 22, 1878 – January 29, 1936) professionally known as Rose Dione was a French-American actress who appeared in numerous silent era and pre-code films. She appeared in 68 films between 1910 and 1932. She was born in Dardilly, Rhône (department) in France, and died in Los Angeles, California. She was known for her role as Madame Tetralini in the film Freaks (1932).
